00044 static const char *report_type_str(int type)
00045 {
00046     switch(type) {
00047         case RPT_DEBUG: return "Debug";
00048         case RPT_INFO: return "Info";
00049         case RPT_OPERATOR: return "Operator";
00050         case RPT_WARNING: return "Warning";
00051         case RPT_ERROR: return "Error";
00052         case RPT_ERROR_INVALID_INPUT: return "Invalid Input Error";
00053         case RPT_ERROR_INVALID_CONTEXT: return "Invalid Context Error";
00054         case RPT_ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY: return "Out Of Memory Error";
00055         default: return "Undefined Type";
00056     }
00057 }

00071 void BKE_reports_clear(ReportList *reports)
00072 {
00073     Report *report, *report_next;
00074 
00075     if (!reports)
00076         return;
00077 
00078     report= reports->list.first;
00079 
00080     while (report) {
00081         report_next= report->next;
00082         MEM_freeN((void *)report->message);
00083         MEM_freeN(report);
00084         report= report_next;
00085     }
00086 
00087     reports->list.first= reports->list.last= NULL;
00088 }

00090 void BKE_report(ReportList *reports, ReportType type, const char *message)
00091 {
00092     Report *report;
00093     int len;
00094 
00095     /* in background mode always print otherwise there are cases the errors wont be displayed,
00096      * but still add to the report list since this is used for python exception handling */
00097     if (G.background || !reports || ((reports->flag & RPT_PRINT) && (type >= reports->printlevel))) {
00098         printf("%s: %s\n", report_type_str(type), message);
00099         fflush(stdout); /* this ensures the message is printed before a crash */
00100     }
00101 
00102     if (reports && (reports->flag & RPT_STORE) && (type >= reports->storelevel)) {
00103         char *message_alloc;
00104         report= MEM_callocN(sizeof(Report), "Report");
00105         report->type= type;
00106         report->typestr= report_type_str(type);
00107 
00108         len= strlen(message);
00109         message_alloc= MEM_callocN(sizeof(char)*(len+1), "ReportMessage");
00110         memcpy(message_alloc, message, sizeof(char)*(len+1));
00111         report->message= message_alloc;
00112         report->len= len;
00113         BLI_addtail(&reports->list, report);
00114     }
00115 }

00117 void BKE_reportf(ReportList *reports, ReportType type, const char *format, ...)
00118 {
00119     DynStr *ds;
00120     Report *report;
00121     va_list args;
00122 
00123     if (G.background || !reports || ((reports->flag & RPT_PRINT) && (type >= reports->printlevel))) {
00124         va_start(args, format);
00125         vprintf(format, args);
00126         va_end(args);
00127         fprintf(stdout, "\n"); /* otherise each report needs to include a \n */
00128         fflush(stdout); /* this ensures the message is printed before a crash */
00129     }
00130 
00131     if (reports && (reports->flag & RPT_STORE) && (type >= reports->storelevel)) {
00132         report= MEM_callocN(sizeof(Report), "Report");
00133 
00134         ds= BLI_dynstr_new();
00135         va_start(args, format);
00136         BLI_dynstr_vappendf(ds, format, args);
00137         va_end(args);
00138 
00139         report->message= BLI_dynstr_get_cstring(ds);
00140         report->len= BLI_dynstr_get_len(ds);
00141         BLI_dynstr_free(ds);
00142 
00143         report->type= type;
00144         report->typestr= report_type_str(type);
00145 
00146         BLI_addtail(&reports->list, report);
00147     }
00148 }

00150 void BKE_reports_prepend(ReportList *reports, const char *prepend)
00151 {
00152     Report *report;
00153     DynStr *ds;
00154 
00155     if (!reports)
00156         return;
00157 
00158     for (report=reports->list.first; report; report=report->next) {
00159         ds= BLI_dynstr_new();
00160 
00161         BLI_dynstr_append(ds, prepend);
00162         BLI_dynstr_append(ds, report->message);
00163         MEM_freeN((void *)report->message);
00164 
00165         report->message= BLI_dynstr_get_cstring(ds);
00166         report->len= BLI_dynstr_get_len(ds);
00167 
00168         BLI_dynstr_free(ds);
00169     }
00170 }

00229 char *BKE_reports_string(ReportList *reports, ReportType level)
00230 {
00231     Report *report;
00232     DynStr *ds;
00233     char *cstring;
00234 
00235     if (!reports || !reports->list.first)
00236         return NULL;
00237 
00238     ds= BLI_dynstr_new();
00239     for (report=reports->list.first; report; report=report->next)
00240         if (report->type >= level)
00241             BLI_dynstr_appendf(ds, "%s: %s\n", report->typestr, report->message);
00242 
00243     if (BLI_dynstr_get_len(ds))
00244         cstring= BLI_dynstr_get_cstring(ds);
00245     else
00246         cstring= NULL;
00247 
00248     BLI_dynstr_free(ds);
00249     return cstring;
00250 }

00276 int BKE_reports_contain(ReportList *reports, ReportType level)

00278     Report *report;
00279     if (reports != NULL) {
